"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-golf-olympic-medals-caddies-paris-2024-b2590122.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Golf caddies are a vital part of the Paris 2024 Olympics as they remain integral to the performance of each golfer  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Caddies are instrumental to their golfer's success, with no player able to win atParis 2024without their adviser on the bag as they trudge round the course.\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, caddies do not receive an Olympic medal if their golfer makes it onto anOlympicpodium.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Golfreturned to the Summer Games at Rio 2016, after it was first introduced as an Olympic event at Paris 1900.\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1900_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6768809597562506e-24, \"text\": \"Paris 1900\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1900_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1900_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But a lack of entries meant that the sport did not become a fixture at the Games throughout the 20thcentury.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was until it was reintroduced more than a century later, with Great Britain's Justin Rose winning gold at the coveted competition.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1005, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997395263089948, \"rank\": 0.00026040953342736117, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Justin Rose\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Rose\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This sparked a conversation around whether caddies - who have a significant influence on any golfer's performance - should be awarded medals as well.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After winning gold in Tokyo, USA'sXander Schauffelewished to present his caddy, Austin Kaiser, with a symbol of his appreciation, and so the 30-year-old and his family gifted him a golden ring, illustrating the US flag above the Olympic rings.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9950245260068972, \"rank\": 0.0050002428560969895, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"score\": 0.9416911164293558, \"rank\": 0.03271933141015339, \"text\": \"Austin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\"}, {\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"score\": 0.9466883279355132, \"rank\": 0.0509768396252646, \"text\": \"Kaiser\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\"}, {\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They knew it meant a lot to me, too,\\\" Kaiser told the Associated Press on Thursday, after the opening round at Le Golf National.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"score\": 0.9466883279355132, \"rank\": 0.0509768396252646, \"text\": \"Kaiser\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999958016393886, \"rank\": 3.960850436599468e-06, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not get my own medal and they wanted to do something special for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US Olympic and Paralympic Committee introduced the \\\"Order of Ikkos\\\" in 2009, allowing medallists to express their gratitude to a member of team by gifting them a medallion.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Kuchar's caddy, John Wood, broke down in tears after having a medallion placed around his neck when the American won bronze at Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Kuchar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Kuchar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Kuchar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Kuchar\"}, {\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Wood_(English_actor)\", \"score\": 0.4340829453262444, \"rank\": 0.6446191797718308, \"text\": \"John Wood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Wood_(English_actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Wood_(English_actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999836057386442, \"rank\": 7.722057710090938e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaiser also admitted to feeling an overwhelming sense of emotion in response to Schauffele's kind gesture four years later.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"score\": 0.9466883279355132, \"rank\": 0.0509768396252646, \"text\": \"Kaiser\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999999374722, \"rank\": 5.281813631077575e-11, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"